            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>The <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KI.xml" title="closure of functions under identity and composition" addr="jms-00KI" type="local">identity function</fr:link> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link> and the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN.xml" title="relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">composition</fr:link> of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjections</fr:link> yields a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-00MD/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MD/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="closure of surjections under identity and composition › forest://jonmsterling/jms-00MD/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00MD.xml" title="closure of surjections under identity and composition" addr="jms-00MD" type="local">closure of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjections</fr:link> under <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00II.xml" title="the identity relation" addr="jms-00II" type="local">identity</fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN.xml" title="relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">composition</fr:link></fr:link> › jms-00MD/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>For the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00KI.xml" title="closure of functions under identity and composition" addr="jms-00KI" type="local">identity function</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we must check that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, there exists an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a'\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a'=a]]></fr:tex>. Of course, we choose <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a' := a]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>

 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\twoheadrightarrow  C]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjections</fr:link>. To show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\circ  f\colon  A\to  C]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link>, we fix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c\in  C]]></fr:tex> to exhibit some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} = c]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  B\twoheadrightarrow  C]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}} = c]]></fr:tex>. Becuase <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00M8.xml" title="surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} = b]]></fr:tex>. Thus we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=g{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}=c]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
